## Example 4 â€” Simplify Expression with Rational Exponents

Simplify $x^{3/4} \cdot x^{1/4}$.

### Step 1: Apply the Product Rule

$$x^{3/4} \cdot x^{1/4} = x^{3/4 + 1/4} = x^{4/4} = x^1 = x$$

### Step 2: Verify in Radical Form

$$x^{3/4} = \sqrt[4]{x^3}, \quad x^{1/4} = \sqrt[4]{x}$$

$$\sqrt[4]{x^3} \cdot \sqrt[4]{x} = \sqrt[4]{x^3 \cdot x} = \sqrt[4]{x^4} = x \checkmark$$

### Step 3: Note

Rational exponents follow the same laws as integer exponents â€” the product rule, quotient rule, and power rule all apply.

âś… Answer: $x^{3/4} \cdot x^{1/4} = x$.

