## Example 5 â€” Convert Between Radical and Exponential Form

**(a)** Convert $\sqrt[5]{x^3}$ to exponential form.

**(b)** Convert $x^{7/2}$ to radical form.

### Step 1: Convert (a)

$$\sqrt[5]{x^3} = x^{3/5}$$

The root index (5) becomes the denominator; the power (3) becomes the numerator.

### Step 2: Convert (b)

$$x^{7/2} = \sqrt[2]{x^7} = \sqrt{x^7}$$

### Step 3: Simplify (b) if Possible

$$\sqrt{x^7} = \sqrt{x^6 \cdot x} = \sqrt{x^6} \cdot \sqrt{x} = x^3\sqrt{x}$$

### Step 4: Verify

$$(x^3\sqrt{x})^2 = x^6 \cdot x = x^7 \checkmark$$

âś… Answer: (a) $\sqrt[5]{x^3} = x^{3/5}$; (b) $x^{7/2} = x^3\sqrt{x}$.

